<doc id="73342" wikidata="Q846564" url="?curid=73342" title="Conjunctive normal form">
<text>In Boolean algebra, a formula is in conjunctive normal form (CNF) or clausal normal form if it is a conjunction of one or more clauses, where a clause is a disjunction of literals; otherwise put, it is a product of sums or an AND of ORs.

In automated theorem proving, the notion &quot;clausal normal form&quot; is often used in a narrower sense, meaning a particular representation of a CNF formula as a set of sets of literals.

==Definition==
A logical formula is considered to be in CNF if it is a conjunction of one or more disjunctions of one or more literals. As in disjunctive normal form (DNF), the only propositional operators in CNF are or (formula_1), and (formula_2), and not (formula_3). The &quot;not&quot; operator can only be used as part of a literal, which means that it can only precede a propositional variable.

The following is a context-free grammar for CNF:
# &quot;CNF&quot; → (&quot;Disjunction&quot;) formula_4 &quot;CNF&quot;
# &quot;CNF&quot; → (&quot;Disjunction&quot;)
# &quot;Disjunction&quot; → &quot;Literal&quot; formula_5 &quot;Disjunction&quot;
# &quot;Disjunction&quot; → &quot;Literal&quot;
# &quot;Literal&quot; → formula_3&quot;Variable&quot;
# &quot;Literal&quot; → &quot;Variable&quot;
Where &quot;Variable&quot; is any variable.

All of the following formulas in the variables formula_7, and formula_8 are in conjunctive normal form:

* formula_9
* formula_10
* formula_11
* formula_12

The following formulas are not in conjunctive normal form:
* formula_13, since an AND is nested within a NOT
*formula_14, since an OR is nested within a NOT
* formula_15, since an AND is nested within an OR

==Conversion to CNF==
In classical logic each propositional formula can be converted to an equivalent formula that is in CNF. This transformation is based on rules about logical equivalences: double negation elimination, De Morgan&#x27;s laws, and the distributive law.

=== Basic algorithm ===
The algorithm to compute a CNF-equivalent of a given propositional formula formula_16 builds upon formula_17 in disjunctive normal form (DNF): step 1.
Then formula_18 is converted to formula_19 by swapping ANDs with ORs and vice versa while negating all the literals. Remove all formula_20.

